text.tspan: Deaths caused by smallpox as a share of all deaths in London
In London in the 18th century around 1 in every 13 deaths was caused by smallpox, the majority of which were young
Data source: Guy (1882) and several Registrar-General summaries of causes of death in London, compiled by Our World in Data.
